      "answer": "**Hermes** is the JS engine Meta built specifically for React Native, optimized for mobile constraints rather than long-running server workloads.\n\nIts key trick is **ahead-of-time compilation to bytecode (`.hbc`)** at build time. The app ships precompiled bytecode instead of raw JS source, so at startup the engine skips the expensive parse-and-compile step and starts executing almost immediately — the main driver of Hermes's faster **TTI** (time to interactive).\n\nThe nuance: Hermes deliberately ships without a JIT to favor low memory use and small size, and its bytecode is memory-mappable, so the OS can lazily page it in instead of loading everything up front.\n\n**Hermes wins TTI by shipping precompiled bytecode, not by being a faster interpreter.**",
