      "answer": "`FlatList` (via `VirtualizedList`) mounts only the rows near the viewport and replaces off-screen rows with blank spacers sized to preserve scroll position, so mount cost and memory stay roughly constant instead of scaling with the dataset.\n\n- `windowSize` — how much content stays mounted, measured in **viewport-heights** (default `21`: the visible screen plus ~10 screens above and below). Lower it to cut memory; too low causes blank flashes on fast scroll.\n- `initialNumToRender` — rows rendered in the very first pass. Tune it to roughly fill the first screen for fast time-to-interactive; extra rows just delay first paint.\n- `maxToRenderPerBatch` — rows added per incremental batch while scrolling. Higher fills gaps faster but does more JS work per frame; lower keeps frames smooth at the cost of more visible blanks.\n\nSenior nuance: these trade **blank space vs JS-thread load**; tune them alongside `removeClippedSubviews` and `updateCellsBatchingPeriod` rather than one in isolation.\n\n**Every FlatList tuning knob trades blank space for JS-thread work — there's no setting that removes the trade-off.**",
