      "question": "In expo-router, how do files map to routes, and what does `_layout.tsx` do?",
      "answer": "expo-router is a **file-based** router built on React Navigation: every file in the `app/` directory becomes a route, and the path becomes the URL. `app/index.tsx` is `/`, `app/profile.tsx` is `/profile`, and `app/users/[id].tsx` is a dynamic route like `/users/42`.\n\nA `_layout.tsx` declares the **navigator** that wraps the routes in its directory (`Stack`, `Tabs`, `Drawer`) or renders children directly with `Slot`. It is where you put shared UI, providers, and per-screen options, and it stays mounted while its child routes change.\n\n- Folders group routes and can each carry their own `_layout`\n- `(group)` parentheses create a route group that organizes files **without** adding a URL segment\n- `+not-found.tsx` handles unmatched paths\n\n**In expo-router, the file tree is the router — a file's path and name is its route.**",
      "level": "junior"
