      "category": "navigation",
      "categoryLabel": "NAVIGATION",
      "question": "Explain route params vs search params in expo-router, and the hooks to read each.",
      "answer": "Both arrive as strings on the same params object but come from different parts of the URL. **Route (path) params** are the dynamic segments declared by the filename, like `[id]` in `app/users/[id].tsx`, and are required to render that screen. **Search params** are the query string, like `?sort=asc`, and are optional.\n\nRead them with `useLocalSearchParams()` for params scoped to **this** screen, or `useGlobalSearchParams()` for params from the currently focused URL anywhere in the tree. A senior nuance: `useGlobalSearchParams` re-renders on **every** navigation change, so prefer `useLocalSearchParams` in deep screens to avoid spurious renders, and since everything is a string, coerce types yourself. Use `[...rest].tsx` for catch-all segments.\n\n**Route params are required and come from the filename; search params are optional and come from the query string.**",
      "level": "senior"
