      "question": "How does deep linking work in expo-router, and how does it relate to React Navigation underneath?",
      "answer": "expo-router is a file-based layer over **React Navigation**: your `app/` tree compiles into a navigator config and a linking config automatically, so the URL is the source of truth for navigation state. Because paths map to files, deep links work out of the box: an incoming URL like `myapp://users/42` or an https App/Universal Link resolves to the matching route and params with no hand-written `linking` config.\n\nUnderneath, React Navigation still owns the **navigation state tree** and reconciles it from the URL; expo-router just generates that tree from the filesystem. Senior nuances: declare the custom `scheme` in app config and host an `apple-app-site-association` (iOS) and `assetlinks.json` (Android) for https links, deep-linking to a nested screen builds a sensible back stack, and you can inspect links with `Linking.getInitialURL()` and the `useURL()` hook.\n\n**expo-router generates React Navigation's linking config from your file tree — deep links just work because the URL already is the route.**",
