      "question": "How do platform-specific files (.ios/.android) work, and how do you handle permissions in an Expo app?",
      "answer": "Metro resolves platform extensions automatically: importing `./Foo` with no extension picks `Foo.ios.tsx`, `Foo.android.tsx` (also `.native` and `.web`) per platform, so you can fork an implementation without runtime branching. `Platform.OS` and `Platform.select` cover smaller inline differences.\n\nPermissions are two parts: a runtime request API on the relevant module (e.g. `requestCameraPermissionsAsync`) plus a native declaration the OS requires — `NSCameraUsageDescription` in `Info.plist` and a `uses-permission` entry in `AndroidManifest.xml`.\n\nThe senior nuance: those native declarations should come from the module's config plugin or the `ios`/`android.permissions` fields in app config rather than hand edits, and on iOS accessing a protected API with no usage-description string makes the OS terminate the app outright, not just deny the prompt.\n\n**A permission needs both a runtime request and a native usage-description string — skip the second and the OS kills the app outright.**",
